
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-li-isis-spp-extensions-00.txt'>
    <title>"IS-IS Extensions for Segment Path Programming", Zhenbin Li, Nan Wu</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-li-isis-spp-extensions-00.txt</link>
    <description>Segment Routing (SR) facilitates the steering of unicast traffic through leveraging the source routing paradigm.  As introduced in Segment Path Programming (SPP), the concept of segment could be used in a more generalized manner that may be beyond reachability.  This document describes the necessary IS-IS extensions for those cases.</description>
    <dc:date>2016-03-21T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
